  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nBefore logging in, it's possible to remove any account from device. It's not even required to input any password.\r\nI think such feature should be secured with account authentication.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"565\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/da130f81-3fd1-45bd-bbc0-0cbb6cd7a47e\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAccount removal is only possible after authentication.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nAccount removal is possible without authentication.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Open Status\r\n2. Create an account, if you don't have any\r\n3. Click the meatball button next to an account\r\n4. A menu with \"Remove this account from device\" opens.\r\n",
