    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @igor-sirotin,\r\nThank you for reporting the issue. We discussed this with the design meeting and this is expected behaviour. Because,\r\n1. Even if we hide account removal behind authentication, someone who has access to your device can always clear data of the app. (Account is gone)\r\n2. And by allowing users to remove accounts from his/her device without authentication, we are allowing him/her to get rid of accounts that are not accessible anymore. (Password forgotten/Owner of the particular account/profile is not available anymore)",
